WEBVTT

00:07.355 --> 00:10.358
THIS IS POINTLESS. I HAVE READ
THE SAME SENTENCE 10 TIMES.

00:10.358 --> 00:12.403
WHAT ARE YOU THINKING?

00:12.403 --> 00:15.450
JUST THAT WE HAVE
TO TELL HER...MAGGIE.

00:15.450 --> 00:17.452
WE'RE NOT BEING
FAIR TO HER.

00:17.452 --> 00:18.757
I MEAN, OBVIOUSLY WE'RE
NOT BEING FAIR TO HER.

00:18.757 --> 00:20.846
YOU'RE CHEATING,
AND I'M LYING,

00:20.846 --> 00:22.631
BUT THE POINT IS,
WE'RE NOT MAKING
THE SITUATION ANY BETTER

00:22.631 --> 00:23.980
BY GOING BEHIND HER BACK.

00:23.980 --> 00:25.851
SHE DESERVES TO KNOW.

00:28.115 --> 00:30.160
WHY? WHAT WERE
YOU THINKING?

00:30.160 --> 00:32.380
THAT.

00:32.380 --> 00:34.338
WELL...THAT...

00:34.338 --> 00:35.861
PLUS...

00:35.861 --> 00:38.255
I'D LOVE TO HAVE SEX
WITH YOU RIGHT NOW.

00:38.255 --> 00:40.605
NED! OOH!

00:40.605 --> 00:41.954
BE SERIOUS.

00:41.954 --> 00:43.391
THAT'S THE THING.
I AM SERIOUS.

00:43.391 --> 00:47.264
I AM TOTALLY,
COMPLETELY SERIOUS.

00:47.264 --> 00:49.136
I'M SUBLIMATING,
AREN'T I?

00:49.136 --> 00:50.485
TOTALLY.

00:50.485 --> 00:52.139
I'M SEEKING
PHYSICAL PLEASURE

00:52.139 --> 00:54.663
AS A DISTRACTION
FROM MY OWN
MORAL CULPABILITY.

00:54.663 --> 00:56.752
PRETTY MUCH.

00:56.752 --> 00:59.581
WE HAVE TO TELL HER.
WE HAVE TO TELL HER.

00:59.581 --> 01:02.018
I...HAVE SOME CONCERNS

01:02.018 --> 01:04.238
ABOUT YOUR BLOOD WORK.

01:04.238 --> 01:08.851
NORMALLY, WE LIKE TO SEE
A PLATELET COUNT OF SEVERAL
HUNDRED THOUSAND.

01:08.851 --> 01:11.419
RIGHT NOW,
YOU'RE AT 68,000.

01:11.419 --> 01:14.030
AND YOUR LIVER FUNCTIONS
ARE ELEVATED.

01:14.030 --> 01:16.946
WH-WHAT--WHAT DOES
ALL THAT MEAN?

01:16.946 --> 01:18.904
I DON'T UNDERSTAND
WHAT ANY OF THAT IS.

01:18.904 --> 01:20.906
YOU ARE IN
THE BEGINNING STAGES

01:20.906 --> 01:22.908
OF SOMETHING CALLED
HELLP SYNDROME.

01:22.908 --> 01:27.435
REMEMBER WHEN WE TALKED
ABOUT YOUR TOXEMIA,
PREECLAMPSIA?

01:27.435 --> 01:31.221
WELL, IN HELLP SYNDROME,
THE LIVER BECOMES INVOLVED.

01:31.221 --> 01:33.963
MY LIVER?!

01:33.963 --> 01:34.964
GOD!

01:34.964 --> 01:37.053
OK, SO...

01:37.053 --> 01:40.056
WHAT DO WE DO? I MEAN,
HOW DO WE TAKE CARE OF THIS?

01:40.056 --> 01:42.450
I'M GONNA DO
SOME MORE BLOOD WORK
AND LIVER STUDIES.

01:42.450 --> 01:44.365
I'M GONNA WANT YOU
TO COLLECT YOUR URINE

01:44.365 --> 01:46.541
SO THAT WE CAN CONTINUE
TO CHECK PROTEIN LEVELS.

01:46.541 --> 01:48.847
OK.

01:48.847 --> 01:50.632
THIS, UH...

01:50.632 --> 01:52.286
THIS SOUNDS BAD.

01:52.286 --> 01:53.852
I MEAN,
THIS SOUNDS DIFFERENT.

01:53.852 --> 01:56.072
YOU NEVER SAID ANYTHING
ABOUT THIS BEFORE.

01:56.072 --> 01:58.640
THROUGH ALL THE EARLY LABOR
AND THE BED REST STUFF--

01:58.640 --> 02:01.164
I MEAN, TOXEMIA, YEAH,
BUT NOT THIS.

02:01.164 --> 02:04.428
CHARLIE...SOMETIMES THIS IS
VERY HARD TO DIAGNOSE.

02:06.126 --> 02:07.910
IS THERE A REAL RISK HERE?

02:07.910 --> 02:09.999
I MEAN, COULD SOMETHING
ACTUALLY HAPPEN TO HER?

02:13.002 --> 02:13.916
YES.

02:21.619 --> 02:24.796
♪ EVERYBODY WANTS TO LIVE ♪

02:24.796 --> 02:26.276
♪ LIKE THEY WANNA LIVE ♪

02:26.276 --> 02:29.584
♪ AND EVERYBODY
WANTS TO LOVE ♪

02:29.584 --> 02:30.933
♪ LIKE THEY WANNA LOVE ♪

02:30.933 --> 02:34.893
♪ AND EVERYBODY
WANTS TO BE ♪

02:34.893 --> 02:39.898
♪ CLOSER TO FREE... ♪

02:53.085 --> 02:55.436
UM, ARE YOU SURE THAT THIS
IS THE RIGHT NEIGHBORHOOD?

02:55.436 --> 02:56.785
'CAUSE IT LOOKS A LITTLE--

02:56.785 --> 02:58.482
I TOLD THE GUY
AT THE TOURIST DESK

02:58.482 --> 03:00.571
HOW MUCH I COULD SPEND
ON A HOTEL.

03:00.571 --> 03:03.270
HE SAID THIS WAS JUST
ABOUT THE ONLY THING
IN MY PRICE RANGE.

03:03.270 --> 03:05.097
ARE THE NUMBERS
GOING UP OR DOWN?

03:05.097 --> 03:06.534
UM, DOWN, I THINK.

03:06.534 --> 03:07.883
ARE YOU SURE YOU DON'T
WANT ME TO--

03:07.883 --> 03:10.799
OH, I GOT IT. REALLY.

03:10.799 --> 03:15.412
UM, HANNAH, HAVE YOU
TALKED TO YOUR PARENTS?

03:15.412 --> 03:17.371
I'M SORRY. I MEAN, I KNOW
IT'S NONE OF MY BUSINESS,

03:17.371 --> 03:18.981
BUT MAYBE IF YOU
TALKED TO THEM.

03:18.981 --> 03:22.071
I CAN'T TALK TO THEM.HOW DO YOU KNOW THAT?

03:22.071 --> 03:25.422
YOU KNOW? MAYBE YOU CAN.
MAYBE THEY'D SURPRISE YOU.

03:25.422 --> 03:28.817
LOOK, MY MOM WAS A YEAR
YOUNGER THAN I AM NOW

03:28.817 --> 03:30.949
WHEN SHE GOT PREGNANT
FOR THE FIRST TIME, OK?

03:30.949 --> 03:33.300
SHE AND MY DAD
HAD 3 KIDS

03:33.300 --> 03:36.259
BY THE TIME
THEY WERE 24, SO...

03:36.259 --> 03:39.044
I DON'T THINK THEY'RE
THE PEOPLE TO TALK TO
ABOUT MY OPTIONS,

03:39.044 --> 03:40.872
BECAUSE AS FAR
AS THEY'RE CONCERNED,

03:40.872 --> 03:42.918
I DON'T HAVE ANY.

03:42.918 --> 03:46.965
AND...MAYBE I DON'T.

03:46.965 --> 03:48.967
I MEAN, THEY DID IT,
RIGHT?

03:48.967 --> 03:51.100
THEY HAD A KID
BEFORE THEY WERE READY.

03:51.100 --> 03:53.581
YEAH, PEOPLE DO DO IT.

03:53.581 --> 03:56.714
YEAH. WOMEN DO IT
ALL THE TIME.

03:56.714 --> 03:59.239
EVEN BY THEMSELVES,
RIGHT?

04:02.154 --> 04:04.026
YOU KNOW WHAT?

04:04.026 --> 04:07.203
WHY DON'T YOU
LET ME TAKE THIS
THE REST OF THE WAY.

04:07.203 --> 04:08.117
THANKS.

04:16.865 --> 04:18.867
MAYBE WE'RE GETTING
ALL NERVOUS FOR NOTHING.

04:18.867 --> 04:20.738
I MEAN, MAYBE
SHE ALREADY KNOWS.

04:20.738 --> 04:22.653
SHE SENSED IT COMING.
WOMEN DO THAT.

04:22.653 --> 04:24.089
MAYBE SHE WAS THINKING

04:24.089 --> 04:25.961
SHE WAS GONNA HAVE
TO BREAK UP WITH ME.

04:25.961 --> 04:27.571
MAYBE SHE'LL
BE RELIEVED.

04:27.571 --> 04:29.965
VERY POSSIBLE.

04:29.965 --> 04:31.575
OK, THEN.

04:33.969 --> 04:35.666
[CRYING]

04:35.666 --> 04:38.452
I--I JUST HEARD.

04:40.976 --> 04:42.194
YOU HEARD?

04:42.194 --> 04:44.501
CHESTER.

04:44.501 --> 04:48.505
HE WAS--MY BROTHER'S
GIRLFRIEND,

04:48.505 --> 04:51.508
